You should try the mobile payment option in India where you can pay almost everywhere where there is a QR code. It's safe, secure & cashless. For foreigners, you can research about the UPI One World payment option where possibly you get a digital wallet where you can load money & make payments anywhere where a merchant or person accepts payment via the QR code. You can see how the local Indians make payments using their mobile phone just by scanning the QR code at any shop or hotel. Maybe you should try so that you don't need to keep searching for an ATM machine or bank to withdraw cash. It's not that cash can be avoided completely but you can carry less cash. You always have an option to insist the merchant to take money via the QR code rather than physical cash saying you are not carrying much cash or don't have cash.
